---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Knee & ACL Injuries"
	heroSubtitle="Knee injuries can be frustrating, especially when they stop you training, competing or even moving comfortably day-to-day."
	breadcrumb="Knee Injuries"
	seoTitle="Knee & ACL Injury Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert knee and ACL injury treatment in Clapham. Our specialist team guides you through rehab and return-to-sport, whether post-surgery or managing ongoing knee pain."
	introImage="/condition/knee-injuries/basketball-women.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/knee-injuries/rugby-tackle.jpg"
	intro={[
		"At Balance Performance Physiotherapy, we help you recover properly and rebuild confidence in your knee. From ACL injuries and post-surgery rehab to ongoing knee pain, we guide you back to full movement and performance.",
		"Our sports injury specialists, physiotherapists, sports podiatrists, strength and conditioning coaches and sports psychologists combine hands-on treatment with gym-based rehabilitation.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get your knee"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsList={[
		"A popping sensation at the time of injury",
		"Swelling after twisting, landing or impact",
		"Feeling of instability or knee \"giving way\"",
		"Locking, catching or sharp pain in the joint",
		"Difficulty fully straightening or bending the knee",
		"Pain around the kneecap during running, stairs or squatting",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="knee injuries"
	treatmentIntro="We focus on building strength, control and confidence so you can return to activity safely. Treatment may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy assessment and diagnosis to determine structural injury",
		"Physiotherapy to restore movement and reduce pain",
		"Strength and conditioning to rebuild muscle and joint support",
		"Tailored rehab programmes",
		"Balance and control training to improve stability",
		"Gradual return-to-sport planning and execution",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Post-ACL surgery patients",
		"Non-surgical ACL rehabilitation patients",
		"Football, rugby and netball players",
		"Winter and urban athletes",
		"Runners with knee pain",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Do I always need surgery for an ACL injury?", a: "Not always. Some people can return to sport with structured rehabilitation alone." },
		{ q: "When can I start running after ACL surgery?", a: "Usually a few months in, once strength and control are ready and sport-specific rehabilitation is completed." },
		{ q: "What is return-to-sport rehab?", a: "A structured plan that builds you back to full training and competition safely." },
		{ q: "Can you help with a locked knee?", a: "Yes. assessment determines the cause and next steps." },
		{ q: "How long does rehab take?", a: "Several months typically to return to full sport, depending on the injury." },
		{ q: "Is hydrotherapy useful?", a: "Yes. it's useful in early rehab for movement with reduced joint load and for leg strengthening." },
	]}
/>
